  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 83c7d752eb2eff945a8f453403991ecd, type: 3}
  m_Name: TheCrone
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::DialogueData
  npcName: The Crone
  soulAvt: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 4f473e6821d83874abb1b2d0f6c9df16, type: 3}
  lines:
  - Oh, I wonder where this is?
  - This is Limbo, a place souls must pass through after their lifespan ends, awaiting
    karmic judgment.
  - What a strange place! Dearie, would you kindly lead the way? My eyesight is too
    poor.
  - ...
  - What's wrong, dearie? Did you say anything? It seems like I fail to catch it.
  - Many souls who come here seem unhappy with life. They wonder, is living in this
    mortal world worthwhile?
  - Oh my, you're asking this old lady such a difficult question! But whether it's
    worthwhile or not is very complicated to say. I don't know how to explain it
    to you. When I was young, I was a street vendor, with no time to think about
    anything else except for making earns. Then, in my old age, I lived alone with
    no children or grandchildren, and I was content with myself.
  - To put it simply, you only live your own life, how would you know about other
    people's? So the question is why don't you go experience life for yourself?
  - Experience my own life?
  - There are many things in this world that you can't experience in a lifetime.
    Go see it yourself, then you'll know. But let me tell you something, don't listen
    to people's nonsense advice. If you want to know what's good or bad, there are
    laws. Just be a good citizen and obey the law, then we'll figure things out later.
  - That's hard to understand.
  - " It\u2019s truly a lot, that\u2019s why you'll understand eventually. I'm just
    saying this because you're an honest dearie. How you live your life is up to
    you."
  - "Live my own life. Find out for myself. Hmm, if possible\u2026"
  autoNext: 000000000000010000000000
